data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** It works just like any other unmanaged type:

```csharp
Span<nint> nints = stackalloc nint[5];
Span<nuint> nuints = stackalloc nuint[3];
```

On this 64-bit system, `sizeof(nint)` is 8 bytes. The only caveat is that `sizeof(nint)` requires an `unsafe` context (since the size isn't fixed at compile time), but the `stackalloc` itself works in safe code when assigned directly to a `Span<T>`.
